description.narrative: (Lebanon): The Mission will continue the University.Scholarship Program (USP)-Phase VII by providing scholarships to financially.needy but academically meritorious Lebanese public school graduates. In 2015,.USAID awarded a $17.8 million agreement to the American University of Beirut to.implement the seventh phase of the USP. This award will support at least 156.students over the next eight years. Eligible students are Lebanese graduates of.public schools. Around 72 students will enroll in August 2017, and at least an.additional 52 are expected by August 2018. The USP, through previous awards.beginning in 2010, provided 745 scholarships covering the full undergraduate.tuition, stipends, housing or transportation allowance, books and medical.insurance, in majors that have high prospects for meaningful employment. Students.also engage in leadership training and career preparation. This program attributes to the higher education earmark and is directed.by the Congress.
